History: After a performance at the nightclub, Bastet’s Den, Eliza is summoned to meet Lorenzo and Vitale Medici. They threaten to expose their secret (steal their own charity blood donation campaign) if you don't turn over the Skull Heart to them. Cerebella, wanting to please Vitale, is sent alongside Eliza to watch her do her job, but is constantly at odds with her and her servants, Albus and Horace.

She was created by Brain Drain. However, she is a joke character and her existence is not canonical.

Starring Fukua, she battles every playable character (regardless of whether the consumer has purchased the DLC) on the game's roster, excluding herself, in the reverse order of when they were implemented in the game; beginning his quest against Robo-Fortune until he achieves his goal of overcoming Filia, the final boss.

As the threat of war faded however, the patriotic spirit that led to Beowulf's popularity finally crashed; many considering their cameos in other televised media to end their careers on a low note.

Valentine now dutifully serves the Skullgirl, carrying out her will from the shadows. She supports herself, so much of her true nature and personality are unknown.

Descripcion: Double (Japanese: ダ ブ ル) is a monstrous creature that can transform at will and who works under The Trinity, He is responsible for ensuring that the Skull Heart falls into the right hands and manipulating events according to the will of the goddesses. Her current appearance is that of a nun, under the name of Sister Agatha.
History: After capturing Filia and Cerebella, Double is sent to Laboratory 8 Anti-Skullgirl in order to destroy her investigations. Against Marie's wishes, she engages and defeats Peacock, claiming that Marie's old friend had become too great a threat to her goals. Without Marie's knowledge, Double captures Peacock, believing that she would be another potential candidate.

Knowing the current Skullgirl's intent for the death of the entire Medici family, he begins his goal of tracking her down by investigating at the River King Casino, a hangout known to the Medici Mafia. There he is received by Cerebella, mistakenly believing that his intention was to cause harm to the Medici. Despite Big Band's attempt to politely leave her after noting that there was no evidence of the Skullgirl, he is forced to fight Cerebella. After winning, he comments on how he no longer wishes to lose as he also did with the Medici.

Descripcion: Parasoul (Japanese: パ ラ ソ ー ル) is the princess of the Renoir family, of the rulers of the Canopy Kingdom, and Umbrella's older sister. She is the daughter of King Franz and Queen Nancy, the former Skullgirl, and wields the Living Weapon, Krieg, in battle. It is under the command of its elite military force, Garzas Negras.
Likes: Logic, Wine, Chess, Fencing, Training, Tennis, Diplomacy, Philosophy, Black Heron Troops, Secretly See The Glorious Annie: Star Symphony, Her sister Umbrella.

History: Few know the terrors of the Skullgirl as intimately as Parasoul. Seven years ago her mother became the Skullgirl who almost destroyed the world. This tragic past has made Parasoul fiercely protective of his country and family, and these two priorities often conflict. Parasoul is now the Crown Princess of the Canopy Kingdom and the leader of her elite military squad, Black Herons. Wielding the Living Weapon, Krieg, she fights with grace, balance, and cunning to defend her family and destroy the Skull Heart so that no one can repeat her mother's terrible mistake.
